column1: #: description: Parameterized event selection efficiencies as a function of truth MET for events which have all truth decay vertices occurring before the start of the ATLAS calorimeter. Event-level efficiencies are evaluated for events that have truth MET $> 200$ GeV
column3: and have at least one displaced truth decay within the fiducial volume. To satisfy the event-level efficiency
column4: events must then pass the full event selection.

column1: #: keyword phrases: Proton-Proton Scattering | Supersymmetry | SUSY
